sql:
SELECT L.location_name
FROM locations L
WHERE L.population = (
  SELECT MAX(population)
  FROM locations
);

external_knowledge:
- Top-level geographic locations refer to the highest-level locations in the hierarchy (e.g., countries or major divisions);
- Population density is calculated as the total population of a location divided by its total area; 
- For a location to be considered top-level, it should not have a parent location (i.e., province_id is NULL).

- Hierarchical structure is implied by the recursive relationship between locations and provinces; 
- "location details" include location names and IDs; 
- "counts" refer to the number of locations within each province; 
- "populations" and "areas" refer to the aggregated population and area of locations within each province; 
- "ratios" are calculated relative to the total or maximum provincial statistics; 
- "hierarchy level" refers to the recursive level in the location-province hierarchy.
